    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1924-09-13T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1924-09-13T06:00:00-05:00" n="142"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d142">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.348 Z 4/161: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kellogg</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-09-13T12:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 13, 1924—noon</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[Received September 13—11:15 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>377. My 373, September 10, 11 a.m.<note n="2" xml:id="d142fn2">Not
                        printed.</note> The Foreign Office has transmitted to me a permit for the
                    flight of the <hi rend="italic">ZR–3</hi> for passage over Great Britain and
                    Northern Ireland. The permit which must be carried in the airship is valid from
                    the 10th of September to December 31st next.</p>
                <p>I am transmitting it today to the naval officer in charge at Friedrichshafen via
                    the naval attaché at Paris.</p>
                <p>The British High Commissioner at Coblenz has granted the necessary authority for
                    the flight over British occupied territory in Germany.</p>
                <p>The Foreign Office has not yet received authorizations from the Irish Free State
                    and Bermuda but are pressing for their reply.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
